criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. males aged 40-80;

          2. diagnosed with COPD according to the GOLD guidelines;

          3. clinically stable patients without medication changes or exacerbation in two months;

          4. smoking history of more than 10 pack years

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. diagnosed with unstable cardiovascular diseases, significant renal or hepatic
             dysfunction or mental incompetence;

          2. diagnosed with asthma, active pulmonary tuberculosis, diffuse panbronchiolitis, cystic
             fibrosis, clinically significant bronchiectasis, exacerbation of COPD or pneumonia in
             two months;

          3. prescribed immunosuppressive medications.
